Why I'm ignoring 90% of audience building advice in 2025:

Traditional wisdom says:

- Post 3x daily
- Be everywhere
- Create tons of content
- Hope something hits
- Chase follower count

But the math doesnâ€™t add up, and nobody is talking about it.

Content Factory Approach:

- 90 posts per month
- 5% engagement rate
- 1% conversion
- Burned out team
- Vanity metrics
- Zero compound effect

My 90-Day System:

- One painful problem
- One primary platform
- $50 ad-spend boost behind winning posts
- Track saves > likes
- Build content magnets
- Email subs > followers

The 90-day focused approach beats content factory every time.

1. It compounds (each win builds on the last)
2. It converts (subscribers > followers)
3. It scales (proven content = paid amplification)
4. It gives leverage:
1. Turn your winners into ads
2. Build retargeting sequences
3. Own your distribution

Try to be a content factory focusing on vanity metrics and viral hits?

Youâ€™ll lose to focused creators who use their content as a value based funnel into actual lead magnet assets and own their distribution.

And the truth? Being a content factory is begging for burnout.

The real growth isn't posting frequency but it's using focused content that is brimming with value and interesting stories that lead your ICP to leveraged content assets.

Solve one problem deeply, test $50 ad spend on every 2x performer, build email list off the winners and own your distribution.

When it come to content the long game beats spray and pray.
